 compliance with healthcare standards, especially in handling sensitive user data.\r\nStay Updated on Mobile Development Trends: Keep abreast of React Native updates and mobile development trends, implementing best practices and new techniques where applicable.\r\n\r\nQualifications\r\n\r\n2+ Years of Experience in Mobile Development: Strong focus on React Native.\r\nProficiency in JavaScript (ES6+) and React Native: Skilled in React Native frameworks for building cross-platform mobile applications.\r\nExperience with Mobile UI/UX Design: Understanding of best practices for mobile design, including responsive layouts, navigation, and animations.\r\nAPI Integration Skills: Ability to work with RESTful and GraphQL APIs to integrate backend data into the app seamlessly.\r\nFamiliarity with Native Modules: Experience in working with native modules for Android and iOS is a plus.\r\nKnowledge of Mobile Testing: Proficiency in writing unit tests, integration tests, and using testing frameworks like Jest and Detox is a plus.\r\nExperience with Git and CI/CD Pipelines: Proficient in version control (Git) with experience in setting up CI/CD pipelines for mobile apps; familiarity with Bitrise for CI/CD is a plus.\r\n\r\nPreferred Qualifications\r\n\r\nExperience in Digital Health or Wellness Apps: Previous work in health-related applications is an advantage.\r\nKnowledge of App Store Deployment: Experience with deploying apps to the App Store and Google Play, including managing updates and versioning.\r\nUnderstanding of Mobile Analytics and Tracking: Experience with tools like Firebase, Mixpanel, or similar for tracking user behavior."}, {'role': 'user', 'content': "Resume: English\nhttps://www.linkedin.com/in/victor-\nmutwiri/\nmutwirilincoln19@gmail.com\nKenya, Remote\nC O N T A C T\nS t t p s : //www.linkedin.com/in/victor-mutwiri/\nm u t w i rilincoln19@gmail.com\nE D U C A T I O N\nh t t p s : / / g i t h u b .com/Victor-Mutwiri\nReact\nKenya, Remote\nSupabase\nReact\nREST APIS\nReact Native\nBootstrap\nSupabase\nCMS\nJavascript\nTailwind Css\nGIT\nHtml/Css\nNov 2021 - Feb 2024\nBusiness Information Technology\nL A N G U A G E S\n2 0 1 8 - 2 0 2 4\nM O B I L E  /  F R O N T E N D  D E V E L O P E R\nEnglish\nFiverr\nTranslate design mockups and wireframes into high-quality, responsive user\ninterfaces using React.js\nBuild reusable React components and libraries for use across multiple projects\nCollaborate with designers and backend developers to integrate user-facing\nelements with server-side logic\nHello! I am a seasoned Mobile and Frontend Web Developer. I bring a unique ble\nnd of technical skills and creativity to the table. As a Software Developer, I specialize in creating beautiful and functional mobile and web apps that are optimized for user experience. My expertise lies in React and React Native etc.\nParticipate in code reviews to ensure code quality, adherence to best practices,\nand maintainability.\nTroubleshoot and debug issues, providing timely and effective solutions\nCabz Track - Contract (Remote)\nNov 2021 - Feb 2024\nLed a team of mobile app engineers  to build a  crossplatform app for both android and ios using react native\nRaised apps users from 0 - 3000 monthly recurring users through targeted m\narketing\nContributed to the development of website/landing page using React.js\nConducted code reviews\nImplement performance optimization techniques to enhance website speed\nand responsiveness.\nPastelar AI - (Remote)\nAugust 2020 -  Sep 2021\nRegularly update and maintain the website to reflect the latest inventory, pricing, and promotions, providing potential clients with accurate and up-to-date information.\nImplement and optimize content updates, including images and descriptions, to enhance the visual appeal and informativeness of the website.\nContinuously work on improving the user interface to create an engaging and intuitive experience for visitors.\nImplement performance optimization techniques to enhance website speed and responsiveness.\nIdentify and address any front-end issues promptly, working closely with relevant teams to resolve technical challenges and maintain the website's functionality.\nNetwork Support\nFiverr\nJan 2020 -  July 2020\nTranslate design mockups and wireframes into high-quality, responsive user interfaces using React.js\nBuild reusable React components and libraries for use across multiple projects\nCollaborate with designers and backend developers to integrate user-facing elements with server-side logic\nDevelop single-page applications using React Router or similar technologies to create smooth, efficient, and dynamic user experiences.\nParticipate in code reviews to ensure code quality, adherence to best practices, and maintainability.\nTroubleshoot and debug issues, providing timely and effective solutions\nGIT\nGal Baking Services\nFeb 2018 - Feb 2020\nTechnical Assistance"}, {'role': 'user', 'content': "Please provide a detailed analysis of how well this resume matches the job description. Include the following sections:\n1. Key Skills Match: List the skills that align well with the job requirements\n2. Missing Skills: Identify important skills from the job description that are not evident in the resume\n3. Experience Alignment: Evaluate how well the candidate's experience matches the role\n4. Improvement Suggestions: Specific recommendations for strengthening the application\n5. Overall Rating: Score from 1-10 (10 being perfect match) with brief explanation\n\nFocus on concrete evidence from the resume without making assumptions about unlisted skills."}], 'model': 'llama3-8b-8192', 'max_tokens': 2000, 'stop': None, 'temperature': 0.7, 'top_p': 1}}
